      • getData

        public final Map<String,Object> getData()
        Getter method for the parsed data.
        Returns:
        A Map representation of the parsed data: each property in a file can be represented as a key-value pair (i.e. a Map entry) and a single file can be represented as a collection of properties, so that file can then be represented as a collection of key-value pairs (i.e. a Map).

      • isInternal

        public final boolean isInternal()
        Returns boolean indicating if file is internal to Lighthouse--i.e. a file that modifies Lighthouse settings and is not meant to be added to the database to be queried. For example, a .ignore file, which marks certain properties to be ignored, is not meant to be queried and would therefore be an "internal" file.
        Returns:
        true if a file is internal, else false

      • setInternal

        public final void setInternal(boolean bool)
        Setter method for "internal" instance variable. A file is internal if it modifies Lighthouse settings and is not meant to be added to the database to be queried. For example, a .ignore file, which marks certain properties to be ignored, is not meant to be queried and would therefore be an "internal" file.
        Parameters:
        bool - true if a file is internal, else false

      • standardize

        public abstract void standardize(File input)
        Standardizes input File into a Map of keys and values. Each property in a file can be represented as a key-value pair (i.e. a Map entry) and a single file can be represented as a collection of properties, so that file can then be represented as a collection of key-value pairs (i.e. a Map).
        Parameters:
        input - the File to be standardized
